com.amitinside.featureflags

Class Factory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amitinside.featureflags.Factory

  • public class Factory
extends Object
    Factory is used to create configuration factories for Feature or FeatureGroup. This is primarily used by FeatureService to create Feature and FeatureGroup configuration instances. 
     final Factory groupFactory = Factory.make("group1", c -> c.withDescription("My Group 1")
                                                           .withStrategy("strategy1")
                                                           .withProperties(props)
                                                           .withEnabled(false)
                                                           .build());
                                                           
 final Factory featureFactory = Factory.make("group1", c -> c.withDescription("My Group 1")
                                                             .withStrategy("strategy1")
                                                             .withGroups(Lists.newArrayList("group1"))
                                                             .withProperties(props)
                                                             .withEnabled(false)
                                                             .build());
    See Also:
    Feature, FeatureGroup, Strategizable
